SUMMARY:Information: MILDMAY LINE: Saturday 31 May and Sunday 1 June\, a 
 reduced service will run between Willesden Junction and Camden Road all 
 day. Trains will run every 15 minutes. In addition\, on Sunday morning\, 
 the 0915 first train from Gospel Oak to Clapham Junction starts from 
 Shepherds Bush. Customers should use the next train at 0927. The 0951 
 train from Camden Road to Richmond\, and the 0958 train from Camden Road 
 to Clapham Junction will start from Willesden Junction
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20250531T045245Z
UID:17512d34-3ddb-11f0-8a64-6045bd00fbdb
DTSTART:20250531
DTEND:20250601
SUMMARY:Part Closure: MILDMAY LINE: Saturday 31 May and Sunday 1 June\, no 
 service between Camden Road and Stratford. Rail replacement buses will run
  as follows: Service S: Camden Road - Holloway Road (for Piccadilly line) 
 - Highbury & Islington - Canonbury - Dalston Junction (for Dalston 
 Kingsland) - Hackney Central - Homerton - Hackney Wick - Stratford. Use 
 alternative Overground services between Highbury & Islington and Dalston 
 Junction (for Dalston Kingsland). For Caledonian Road & Barnsbury use 
 local bus route 274 to/from Camden Road or walk to / from Highbury & 
 Islington.
END:VEVENT
